<br>
NBG doesn't work, for the simple reason that:<br>
A) You never know if the character actually /needs/ the item, or if they just happen to be that class, and are planning on selling it any damn way.  Just like when Starcryst did the 8th shawl quest and an uber hammer dropped... I was going to roll on it with the intention of selling, but Star (being a really good and honorable guy) told everyone NBG.  NOW, I could have rolled on it, but feeling 'TRUE' NBG, I opted not to.<br>
<br>
Next day, it's in the tunnel.  And yes, it was the same hammer that I could have rolled on, because Star (I believe) was the first person to finish the 8th shawl, and only two hammers were even /on/ the server at that point.<br>
<br>
and<br>
<br>
B) Everyone needs plat.  I don't know anyone who doesn't.<br>
